```mermaid
%% AgriOps — Tenant Isolation (Multi-Tenant Security)
sequenceDiagram

    actor UserA as User (Company A)
    actor UserB as User (Company B)
    participant Django
    participant View as ListView / DetailView
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────
    %% LEGITIMATE REQUEST — OWN DATA
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────

    UserA->>Django: GET /suppliers/ [authenticated, company_id=1]
    Django->>View: SupplierListView.get_queryset()
    View->>View: filter(company=request.user.company)
    Note over View: company_id=1 applied to queryset
    View->>DB: SELECT * FROM suppliers WHERE company_id=1
    DB-->>View: 12 suppliers (all belong to Company A)
    View-->>UserA: 200 — Supplier list (Company A data only)

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────
    %% CROSS-TENANT URL ENUMERATION ATTEMPT
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────

    UserB->>Django: GET /suppliers/99/ [authenticated, company_id=2]
    Note over UserB: Supplier #99 belongs to Company A
    Django->>View: SupplierDetailView.get_object()
    View->>DB: SELECT * FROM suppliers WHERE id=99
    DB-->>View: Supplier record (company_id=1)
    View->>View: Check: obj.company == request.user.company?
    Note over View: company_id=1 ≠ company_id=2
    View->>View: Raise Http404
    Note over View: 404 not 403 — reveals nothing about existence
    View-->>UserB: 404 Not Found

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────
    %% CREATE — COMPANY AUTO-ASSIGNED
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────

    UserA->>Django: POST /suppliers/new/ {name: "New Supplier"}
    Note over UserA: No company field in POST data
    Django->>View: SupplierCreateView.form_valid()
    View->>View: form.instance.company = request.user.company
    Note over View: company_id=1 assigned automatically
    View->>DB: INSERT INTO suppliers (company_id=1, name=...)
    DB-->>View: Supplier created
    View-->>UserA: 302 Redirect to /suppliers/

    %% ─────────────────────────────────────
    %% PHASE 4 — PostgreSQL RLS (additional layer)
    %% ─────────────────────────────────────

    Note over Django,DB: Phase 4: Row-Level Security added at DB layer
    Note over Django,DB: Even if application filter is bypassed,
    Note over Django,DB: PostgreSQL refuses cross-tenant reads.
    Note over Django,DB: Defence-in-depth: two independent isolation layers.
```
